The paper is about a code-search engine that uses various code features to specialize the search process for better querying, searching, and ranking of code-search results. This falls under the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SE) as it deals with improving the software development process. The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques for ranking the search results, which falls under information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper specifically focuses on C/C++ code, which falls under programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also mentions the use of simple code features to capture different aspects of code, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
